# 1.2 Dynamic Selection Logic (Answers)

This section explains how report parameters were dynamically defined in **Answers**, following SQL-based analytical concepts.

The selections below controlled the **raw data extract**, which later fed into Excel RTL templates.

---

## 1.2.1 Market Selection
Markets were selected dynamically depending on client needs:
- Total Market
- Coop
- Migros

These selections acted as **filter conditions**, similar to SQL `WHERE` clauses.

---

## 1.2.2 Product Selection
Product selection was one of the most complex components.

Supported selection types:
- Single products (e.g., ABC)
- Multi-level product hierarchies
- Custom hierarchies built dynamically from **thousands of items**

This required:
- Deep understanding of product taxonomy
- Correct hierarchy roll-ups
- Validation to avoid double counting

---

## 1.2.3 Fact Selection
Facts defined **what metric was being analyzed**:
- Sales Value
- Volume
- Price
- Market Share

Each fact followed predefined KPI calculation rules to ensure consistency across reports.

---

## 1.2.4 Time Selection
Time logic supported multiple business calendars:
- YTD (Year-to-Date)
- MAT (Moving Annual Total)
- Month / Year / Week
- Retail calendars: **4-4-4**
